Hi Justin!! Glad we finally got our old journal back. Brings back loads of memories...Now all we have to do is get Matt to get another journal and it'll be just like the old "alliance." haha. 

It's only Monday and I'm already not having a good week. 

Last night I was up until 1h30 doing my stupid term paper for History. Luckily, I think it turned out great. I only got like, three hours of sleep though, and the past three days, I've been loaded up on painkillers, so I've been nothing but groggy. Not fun.

Now I'm just waiting for Matt to get home and call me. He told me like, two hours ago that he was going to be at his coworker, Cesar's house eating dinner and stuff and I still haven't heard from him. I'm starting to get a bit worried.

But tonight was pretty cool. I got to talk to David and Chris, two friends of Matt's that actually don't drive me crazy. lol. It was good to hear from Chris. I haven't talked to him in forever and a day, and he's like a big brother to me. Too bad we could only talk for ten minutes before he had to go back to work. He's coming down for Christmas for a few days though. So it'll be great to see him again. It's been what, a year since the last time he was here. 

My sister has been bugging me about going to Huntsville this weekend for Heather's birthday party. She wants me to bring one of my girlfriends, go to this party, get trashed, and then have me and said friend stay in a hotel only to leave the next day. My mom's already said no, and all of us are getting really fed up with her. If I'm going to visit her, I'm going to want to spend time with her. 

This weekend I'm going to start getting stuff for Brandy and my dad for their birthdays. Brandy's stuff should be...interesting. haha. My dad...not so sure. I'll probably just get him something silly to have around the house...like a slingshot. He likes things like that...lol. 

By the way, Justin...we should write that detective story...haha. It would be like Nancy Drew on crack. Awesome. 

And now I'm off to continue waiting for Matt to call.

~Friday~

Stayed home sick. Being a girl sucks :( I pretty much just slept till 11, took a buttload of medicine, and then went with my dad to get my hair cut and dyed. It looks so much better!!! I love it! Then I spent the night at my dad's house. Matt came over for a little bit, but had to leave early to go to his mom's house. So my dad and I stayed up until around 1 just watching TV and talking. 

~Saturday~

Had to get up at 6 to get ready for work! My dad and I left the house by 6h45, and waited at the school till Hendrick showed up. I had to work sound for the HOSA convention. It was pretty boring, but I got to watch a video about autism. We left at 10h30 for a break, and came back at noon for another presentation, then it all ended around 3. Matt picked me up and took me home so I could do my chores and whatnot. At around 5 or 6 he picked me up, we went back to his place for a bit, and went out to Bennigan's because we were both hardcore craving some potato soup. haha. When we got back to his place, we watched Final Destination 3. Not a bad movie...not nearly as good as the first, but a lot better than the second. Afterwards Matt put it on some cartoon, and I fell asleep laying my head in his lap. Around 10h30 he woke me up, and started making fun of me and telling me how cute I look laying there with my mouth wide open. Nice. Around 10h45, after I woke up a bit and we cleaned up his room, he took me home. It was a good day :D

~Sunday~

Got up at 6. Went back to sleep. Got up around 10. Hung out with my mom and Dwayne for a bit, and around noon started getting ready to go to Matt's mom's for his his annual birthday bulgogi feast. Yummm!! But everyone aside from us was late. When they all got there, I had to take Matt for a walk so he wouldn't see the cake. It was a mustang cake. It was so cool! So we got back to the house, ate bulgogi, and then we showed him his cake. The look on his face was priceless. So then we destroyed the mustang (much to my delight) and Matt opened his present. Only John and Paul gave him their gift. What they ended up doing was going down every isle at WalMart and got him the most outlandish thing in the isle. It was....interesting. haha. Then Matt and I washed his car, I got really annoyed with John, and we went back to Matt's to hang out and watch TV. Theeeen he took me to my dad's, we hung out there for a little bit, watched Willy Wonka, and then Matt left. My dad and I stayed up watching Cast Away, talking about scary movies and good books. Then around 12h30 my dad went to sleep. Now it's 1h20 in the morning and I'm dreading getting up early and making breakfast for Matt. I've never made French Toast before. I'm scared. Haha. And now I'm off to go find more information for my novel!!

Mwahaha I'm copying Ashley, 'cause that bitch is a genius with good organizational skills.

So how did Molly's day go?

Physics - Did a lab. I realised that I have awful reaction time, and Jessie has fat hands. It's not fun testing your reflexes at 8h00 in the morning.

English - Took a test. I think I did alright. I really can't stand that class, and it bothers me because I love English! Maybe it's the simple fact that the teacher is an arrogant prick, or how the AP/GT students are some of the most closed-minded and stuck-up kids I've ever met. Bastards.

Algebra II - Did some random crap that i couldn't work on since my calculator is so damn old. Not fun.

P.E. - Played badmitton for a little while, until I came to the conclusion that I hate physical activity and everyone in the class makes me mad, so I sat down and read my delightful little book. It brightens my day. 

So now I'm just talking to Ashley and waiting for Matt to get done being that fat cow that he is so we can hang out. Loverly. We might end up going to the movies with John and a bunch of other people, but Stephanie is probably going to be there, so I doubt we'll go. haha. I'm winning the fight!

Well, I had a good day....got to spend the night at my dad's last night, and finally got to see Matthew tonight!! It was only for a couple hours...and one of those hours was spent trying to get John out of Matthew's room. He ended up having to pay John $5 to finally leave, which really made me mad. But after that it was fun. It was great being able to spend some time with Matthew completely uninterrupted. We rarely get to do that anymore. Also got to see Talladega Nights today. Awesome! One of the better movies I've seen lately. 

I'm procrastinating hardcore on my Enlish, Physics, French, and History homework. 

And I've come to the conclusion that I need to get out more and actually hang out with people sometimes. haha. I always say that's going to happen and it never does. I'm destined to be a hermit.

Everyone wants to be loved for who they are, and when this actually happens, people can be taken completely off-guard and feel invincible. When you're very young, you don't understand. You don't understand what's right and what's wrong when it comes to these emotions, as well as actions. And when someone comes along that tells you they love you, that you're completely flawless and you're all they've ever wanted, they have an open shot, ending in one of the worst types of betrayal: abuse of the concept of love. 

But life goes on. Mortal wounds don't heal. They can only be bandaged up and re-opened when changing is in order. And now, now that that person has been found that one would love to hear all of those romantic things from, it doesn't happen. I would love to have that fairy tale relationship, where I'm the centre of my love's world, I mean the world to them, and they want to be together forever. When a person is treated like that, it's simple to ignore all the wrong things that have been done to them. But is it okay to settle with that? What about when you do move on? Are you happy with the person you want to spend your life with that doesn't have an ounce of romance in their body, or long for the one that made you feel like a queen, but completely wronged you? It seems like there is no grey area in this one. 

I guess as you get older, some things never change. Maybe I am self-centered, and maybe I want too much. It just makes me wonder, what happens when the person that made you feel like you were perfect hurt you the most, and the person that you love more than anything makes you feel completely inadequate. 

Most of the time I can look up at the sky and see myself smiling down, but occasionally, I have no idea where I'm at and wonder what I'm thinking. 

(I guess this is what happens when you're up at 3h00 in the morning listening to sad country music after having a depressing conversation with your loved one with a Jennifer Aniston sex scene in the background.)
